Elmer G. Rees, &quot;Notes on Geometry&quot;
Spr ger | 1982 | ISBN: 354012053X | 109 pages | PDF | 1.48 MB

This book offers a concrete and accessible treatment of Euclidean, projective and hyperbolic geometry, with more stress on topological aspects than is found in most textbooks. The author's purpose is to introduce students to geometry on the basis of elementary concepts in linear algebra, group theory,
